{"questionId":"9074267","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A standing sound wave is established in a tube that is closed at one end and open at&nbsp;the other end. The period of the wave is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi></math>. The diagram represents the standing wave&nbsp;at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> and at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>T</mi><mn>8</mn></mfrac></math>. The wavelength of the wave is 1.20 m. Positive displacements&nbsp;mean displacements to the right.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/1770c984c19363e2a7d89be49f2de7dc8ab3022c.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the length of the tube.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>L</em> = «<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"false\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo></mstyle></math>»&nbsp;0.90 «m»&nbsp;✓</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9074267","referenceCode":"21N.2.SL.TZ0.c.i","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Calculate the length of the tube.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 4: Waves","4.5 – Standing waves","Core","Topic 4: Waves"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}